question:
What will be the output when the button is clicked?

Frame f = new Frame();
Button b = new Button("Click");

b.addActionListener(new ActionListener() {
    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
        System.out.println("A");
    }
});

b.addActionListener(new ActionListener() {
    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
        System.out.println("B");
    }
});

f.add(b);
f.setSize(200,200);
f.setVisible(true);

What happens when the window close button is clicked?

Frame f = new Frame();
f.addWindowListener(new WindowAdapter() {
    public void windowClosed(WindowEvent e) {
        System.exit(0);
    }
});
f.setSize(300,300);
f.setVisible(true);

Identify the event triggered when the checkbox state is changed.

Checkbox cb = new Checkbox("Java");

cb.addItemListener(new ItemListener() {
    public void itemStateChanged(ItemEvent e) {
        System.out.println("Changed");
    }
});

What is the result of clicking the button multiple times?

class Test extends Frame implements ActionListener {
    int count = 0;

    public Test() {
        Button b = new Button("Press");
        b.addActionListener(this);
        add(b);
        setSize(200,200);
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
        count++;
        System.out.println(count);
    }
}

What is the output when a key is typed inside the TextField?

TextField tf = new TextField();

tf.addKeyListener(new KeyAdapter() {
    public void keyPressed(KeyEvent e) {
        System.out.print("P");
    }
    public void keyTyped(KeyEvent e) {
        System.out.print("T");
    }
});
